FR940728-1-00009 FR940728-1-00002 (ii) The loss, removal, or closing of a major source or sources of employment in the last 3 years which causes an increase of 2 percentage points or more in the area's most recent unemployment rate compared with the period immediately before the dislocation; (iii) Chronic or long-term economic deterioration, documented by one or both of the following conditions: (A) An unemployment level equal to or over 1.5 times the National average unemployment percentage from 4 out of the last 5 years, starting with the most current statistics available. The applicant, when calculating recent years' unemployment percentages, should compare county statistics with the National Average unemployment for the corresponding year. Statistics on unemployment will be based on figures provided by the Bureau of Labor Statistics; (B) A 15% loss of population due to out-migration over the most recent 10-year decennial census, based on the U.S. Bureau of the Census decennial data; (iv) A designation as a Rural Empowerment Zone or Rural Enterprise Community by the Empowerment Zone Program authorized by Section 13301 of the Omnibus Reconciliation Act of 1993, Public Law 103&hyph;66 (107 Stat. 312), 26 U.S.C. 1391&hyph;1393. (h) *␣*␣* (11) Special economic status _25 points. * * * * * Dated: July 20, 1994. Bob J. Nash, Under Secretary, Small Community and Rural Development. [FR Doc. 94&hyph;18410 Filed 7&hyph;27&hyph;94; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 3410&hyph;15&hyph;P
